00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:49,368
I want him to go number one
in the draft, and I want him to play.

474
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:53,127
It'll either be Denver or San Diego.
He'll go first.

475
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,567
I'll either surf or ski.

476
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:59,401
- Denver's where he should be.
<i>- I'll</i> give it everything.

477
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:04,527
You know I don't do contracts,
but what you do have is my word.

478
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,806
And it's stronger than oak.

479
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:02,603
- Hello.
- Dorothy? Jerry Maguire.

480
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:07,283
- Is Avery there?
- She had an NFL meeting in Atlanta.

481
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:12,841
- Jerry.
- Hello? Hello?

482
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:16,841
Sorry, that was my son and the nanny.

483
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:21,802
- They're in our office?
- Nanny? I prefer child technician.

484
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:26,807
I had the calls transferred
to my house so I could work here.

485
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,480
<i>That's fine. Dorothy, we are back.</i>

486
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:32,883
We are so very, very back.

487
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,202
I re-signed Cush. We're set.

488
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:38,887
- I am so happy for you.
- Happy for us.

489
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:42,408
Happy for us. Okay, happy for us.

490
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:45,246
Rod, being at the draft is good.

491
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:49,769
No, Rod, just get on the plane
and meet us at the gate.

492
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:52,645
- Good. See you there.
- God <i>bless.</i>

493
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:56,327
Avery will meet you
at the B-gate at 4:15.

494
00:39:56,560 --> 00:40:00,485
Do you know the human head
weighs eight pounds?

495
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:07,050
Did you know Troy Aikman, in six
years, has passed for 16,303 yards?

496
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:13,001
- Bees and dogs can smell fear.
- I booked Tidwell at the Marriott.

497
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:15,641
- Does he smoke?
- I don't know.

498
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:21,205
Did you know Pete Rose has 4256 hits
and he's not in the Hall of Fame?

499
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:25,730
Do you know that my neighbor
has three rabbits?

500
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:29,602
I can't compete with that.

501
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:34,250
- So did we go over everything? Yes?
- Yep.

502
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:37,888
- Back on Tuesday, right?
- Yeah.

503
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:43,084
Ray, have fun at school. Wish me luck.

504
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,408
Luck!

505
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:07,928
- Hey, Rod.
- Hey, Jerry...

506
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,565
Cush, how are you, man?

507
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:15,564
Jerry, we should be selling these.

508
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:19,327
This is my agent,
you might want his autograph.

509
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,244
My hand's getting tired.

510
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:24,330
- Excuse me.
- What's happening?

511
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:26,324
Are you Hootie?

512
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:30,565
No, I am not Hootie.

513
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:39,009
What is it gonna be,
San Diego or Denver?

514
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:41,124
I'll surf or ski.

515
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,607
He'll either surf or ski.

516
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:58,930
Rod, at last I find you.

517
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:03,210
Why am I here? It's like I'm
five years late for the prom.

518
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:08,611
- Nobody gives a damn about me.
- Let's walk through this lobby.

519
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:14,250
I want all the media and player reps
to see you for what you are:

520
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:17,489
The best-kept secret in the NFL.

521
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:23,686
The most commanding wide receiver.
You're fast, fierce, charismatic.

522
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:26,645
You're the man.
You are the man! Ready?

523
00:42:26,800 --> 00:42:27,801
Let's go.

524
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:29,689
Let's walk.

525
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:33,883
The fiercest. You are the man.

526
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:38,523
- Let's do it.
- Hi, Mel. Hi, Torn.

527
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:39,921
Where's Cush?

528
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:44,205
Good thing you held onto Cushman.
San Diego or Denver?

529
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:49,844
I want you to meet Rod Tidwell,
110 catches, 1550 yards last year.

530
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:13,447
Now I wanna talk about Rod Tidwell.
A fierce receiver.

531
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:27,686
I came all that way
just to walk the lobby.

532
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:30,004
It might have even worked.

533
00:43:30,240 --> 00:43:33,926
Yeah? Let's do that shit again.

534
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:40,403
Shooting a Reebok ad down there.
Where are my endorsements?

535
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:45,003
I didn't get no love from Chevy,
no love from Pepsi.

536
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:48,801
I didn't get no love from
that Energizer Bunny or Nike.

537
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:51,771
Obviously, I didn't get
love from Reebok.

538
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:56,369
- Did I tell you my Reebok story?
- I gotta get back to Cush.

539
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:01,845
Oh, your golden paycheck.
But wait, I'll boil it down for you.

540
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:03,769
Fuck Reebok!

541
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:06,844
All they do is ignore me.
Always have.

542
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:08,929
Always have.

543
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:14,161
You know what was great down there?
You unloaded that large chip...

544
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:16,044
...on your shoulder.

545
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:18,726
And you let people in.

546
00:44:20,320 --> 00:44:22,243
You were brilliant.

547
00:44:23,320 --> 00:44:24,765
- Brilliant?
- Brilliant.

548
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:28,442
- Really?
- Take care, I'll see you tomorrow.

549
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:32,606
- You love me now?
- I'm about showing you the money!

550
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:36,811
I was just testing you,
but to hear you say that...

551
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:40,408
...makes me love you, baby.
You know?

552
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:42,762
Jerry, come back!

553
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:47,964
- How was your flight?
- Good.

554
00:44:48,280 --> 00:44:50,282
- What size are you?
- 12 and a half.

555
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:54,166
Grab a couple pairs
of them new shoes by the door.

556
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:05,451
Cush, Matt, we have
a decision to make.

557
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:11,402
San Diego just came in with
a last-minute scenario. It's big.

558
00:45:11,680 --> 00:45:13,603
He's got to go number one.

559
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:18,601
San Diego wants to trade up
with Denver. They want him bad.

560
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:23,169
- What about Denver?
- This stuff happens before a draft.

561
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:24,845
San Diego, Matt...

562
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:29,722
...they're offering seven years
for 30. Signing bonus of 8.

563
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:33,606
- Should I unplug the phone?
- Reporters keep calling.

564
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:37,247
You just be friendly
and say, "No comment."

565
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:41,243
I'm no good at talking
and saying nothing.

566
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:45,201
Well, let me...

567
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:49,490
For you, it's a pleasure.
This is Cush.

568
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:54,681
<i>It's Sugar. Is Maguire there?
Sniff if he is.</i>

569
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:58,441
Remember, you're in
with the big boys now.

570
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:02,690
<i>Let your dad talk,
and know that I got you the deal.</i>

571
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:06,447
<i>This is business, not friendship.
Be strong...</i>

572
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:09,001
<i>...because you're global now.</i>

573
00:46:09,240 --> 00:46:13,165
Okay, buddy? See you later.

574
00:46:17,560 --> 00:46:19,130
No comment.

575
00:46:26,080 --> 00:46:28,924
- He's got it wrong.
- You're on TV again.

576
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:31,891
I'm sick of me, already.

577
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:48,522
Before I go back to Denver,
we should put something on paper.

578
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:51,331
Something that says you're with me.

579
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:53,961
Not right now, Jerry.

580
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:03,921
Do I know everything
there is to know here, Matt?

581
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:10,563
You're not talking
with Bob Sugar, are you?

582
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:14,966
Apparently, Denver would only
deal with him.

583
00:47:15,800 --> 00:47:18,690
Said who? Sugar?

584
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:21,085
I'm learning as I go.

585
00:47:21,680 --> 00:47:26,846
So you empowered him
to deal with Denver behind my back?

586
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:29,202
I'm sorry...

587
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:34,003
- I love my son.
- I love your son!

588
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:39,282
I brought Denver to 20 million.
They always deal with me.

589
00:47:39,520 --> 00:47:43,684
You listened to Sugar.
Bob Sugar, Matt, is a child.

590
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:47,601
You let that snake in the door?

591
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:55,724
Listen, rookie mistake.
I'll fix this Denver thing for you.

592
00:47:55,960 --> 00:47:59,009
You didn't sign anything
with Sugar, right?

593
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:05,843
Matt? Tell me you didn't sign.

594
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:09,611
Because I'm still sort of
moved by your...

595
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:13,765
..."my word is stronger
than oak" thing.

596
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:18,324
We signed an hour ago.

597
00:48:19,200 --> 00:48:23,091
You were in the lobby
with the black fella.

598
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:29,607
Sorry, Jerry.
I just want to play football.

599
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:37,242
- What do I do? How do I spin it?
- Honey, it's spun.

600
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:39,881
What did I do to you?

601
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:41,929
It's all about you, isn't it?

602
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:47,160
"Soothe me, save me, love me."
I have to finish my job.

603
00:48:47,440 --> 00:48:49,442
Everything's on the run.

604
00:48:49,680 --> 00:48:53,241
You and I are sales people.
We sell.

605
00:48:53,440 --> 00:48:57,240
It's not "Love me"
or "Trust my handshake"...

606
00:48:57,520 --> 00:49:00,569
...it's "Make the sale!
Get it signed."

607
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:03,445
Jump right into my nightmare.

608
00:49:03,640 --> 00:49:06,086
So now I can't be honest?

609
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:11,320
- I'd prefer loyalty.
- What'd we say when we got together?

610
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:13,443
Brutal truth. Remember?

611
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:16,846
I think you added the "brutal."

612
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:22,484
There's a sensitivity thing that some
people have. I don't have it.

613
00:49:22,720 --> 00:49:25,849
I don't cry at movies,
or gush over babies...

614
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:28,048
...I don't do Christmas early...

615
00:49:28,280 --> 00:49:31,921
...and I don't tell a man who
screwed up our lives:

616
00:49:32,120 --> 00:49:35,806
"Oh, poor baby."
That's me, for better or worse.

617
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:37,849
But I do love you.

618
00:49:41,880 --> 00:49:45,327
- Avery, it's over.
- I didn't hear it.

619
00:49:46,280 --> 00:49:49,887
- Something is missing.
- You've never been alone.

620
00:49:50,080 --> 00:49:52,003
- Listen.
- You can't be alone.

621
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:54,885
It's over.

622
00:49:57,840 --> 00:50:00,730
No one has ever dumped me.

623
00:50:01,880 --> 00:50:04,087
I'm not trying to make history.

624
00:50:04,920 --> 00:50:08,527
I climbed to the top of El Capitan...

625
00:50:08,760 --> 00:50:13,004
...in 18 hours and 23 minutes.
I can make this work.

626
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:17,843
No.

627
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:20,961
Oh, Jerry.

628
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:32,251
I didn't ever want to hurt you.

629
00:50:41,840 --> 00:50:47,244
I won't let you hurt me, Jerry.
I'm too strong for you. Loser!

630
00:50:52,640 --> 00:50:55,928
Roll with the punches.
Tomorrow's another day.

631
00:50:57,680 --> 00:50:59,125
Taxi!

632
00:50:59,560 --> 00:51:02,040
You're loving me now, aren't you?

633
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:05,445
Very much. Taxi!

634
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:09,162
Is it my imagination?
Didn't we arrive in a limo?

635
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:14,810
<i>The question is... I hope I don't
sound like a shrink here, but...</i>

636
00:51:15,640 --> 00:51:20,567
<i>- ...what's wrong?
- Man, I'm just a big disappointment.</i>

637
00:51:20,800 --> 00:51:25,169
Jerry, everybody cries on this show.

638
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:28,211
If you tested positive,
quit doing blow.

639
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:32,651
Upset about your baby?
Why'd you leave her mother?

640
00:51:32,800 --> 00:51:34,165
I knew her, she's okay.

641
00:51:34,400 --> 00:51:39,486
<i>The media don't understand
the pressures $54 million comes with.</i>

642
00:51:39,720 --> 00:51:44,408
- This is some bullshit.
- What are you doing with me, Rod?

643
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:50,246
- What?
- Don't you even see? I'm finished.

644
00:51:50,680 --> 00:51:53,365
I am fucked!

645
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:56,684
Twenty-four hours ago I was hot!

646
00:51:56,920 --> 00:51:58,570
Now...

647
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:01,322
...I'm a cautionary tale.

648
00:52:01,560 --> 00:52:07,010
I don't need this jacket,
because I'm cloaked in failure!

649
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:10,403
I lost him the night before the draft.

650
00:52:10,640 --> 00:52:12,608
Why? Let's recap.

651
00:52:12,800 --> 00:52:17,442
Because a hockey player's kid
made me feel superficial.

652
00:52:17,640 --> 00:52:21,770
I ate some bad pizza, went to bed
and grew a conscience!

653
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:26,450
Well, boo-fucking-hoo!

654
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:31,166
I got a shelf life of 10 years.

655
00:52:31,400 --> 00:52:36,645
My next contract has to bring
the dollars that'll last a long time.

656
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:39,321
I'm done in five years.

657
00:52:39,560 --> 00:52:41,961
What's my family gonna live on?

658
00:52:42,240 --> 00:52:45,244
Huh? What you get me.

659
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:47,408
So I won't hear your shit.

660
00:52:47,680 --> 00:52:52,607
"Oh, I lost Cush and Avery..."

661
00:52:52,840 --> 00:52:55,446
Could I have another drink, please?

662
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:58,684
Anybody else would have
left you by now...

663
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:02,288
...but I'm sticking with you.
I said I would.

664
00:53:02,520 --> 00:53:06,366
If I gotta ride your ass,
you gonna show me the money.

665
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:09,080
You gonna show me the money.

666
00:53:11,600 --> 00:53:16,162
We together on this. You know
what I'm saying? We gonna be one.

667
00:53:18,120 --> 00:53:20,885
The both of us! You know?!

668
00:53:21,120 --> 00:53:23,441
Oh, my God.

669
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:30,570
You have no messages.

670
00:53:56,400 --> 00:54:01,327
He's coming. He just lost his
best client. I invited the guy over.

671
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:06,930
This is not a guy. It's a syndrome.
"Early midlife, hanging by a thread...

672
00:54:07,120 --> 00:54:12,001
...I can't be alone, I'll call
my long-suffering assistant" syndrome.

673
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:16,649
- But if that's what you want...
- Honey, he's engaged.

674
00:54:16,880 --> 00:54:21,408
And for the first time,
I'm part of something I believe in.

675
00:54:21,880 --> 00:54:24,850
Okay. But he better not
be good-looking!

676
00:54:31,040 --> 00:54:32,769
I'm Jerry Maguire.

677
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:38,688
Hello. You're just the way
I pictured you.

678
00:54:39,000 --> 00:54:43,130
- I'm her disapproving sister, Laurel.
- Honesty.

679
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:44,927
Thank you.

680
00:54:47,360 --> 00:54:49,966
Thank you. Dorothy!

681
00:54:53,080 --> 00:54:56,880
Dorothy, your boss is here.

682
00:54:57,360 --> 00:54:58,725
Hello.

683
00:55:02,880 --> 00:55:04,405
Hey, you.

684
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:07,285
- Thanks for inviting me over.
- Sure.

685
00:55:07,520 --> 00:55:11,002
Where's the little guy?

686
00:55:11,280 --> 00:55:13,089
- He's sleeping.
- Sleeping.

687
00:55:15,400 --> 00:55:20,770
I'm so glad you're home.
That alone thing is not my specialty.

688
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:22,761
Oh, my God!

689
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:30,211
Well, I broke up with Avery.

690
00:55:35,920 --> 00:55:40,767
- Gosh, you know, that's too bad.
- No, it's better...

691
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:45,642
...because we'll still be friends.
It's better now than later.

692
00:55:48,720 --> 00:55:52,327
- I'm dying here, aren't I?
- It's a really bad cut.

693
00:55:52,520 --> 00:55:55,842
Just think if I got her
the ring she really wanted.

694
00:56:01,960 --> 00:56:04,201
Why don't you have a seat?

695
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:10,885
I'll get some aloe vera for the cut.

696
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:14,444
- Do you have something to drink?
- Sure.

697
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:21,727
I heard.

698
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:26,090
No kidding. I saw the shadow
of curious shoes under the door.

699
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:30,484
He'd go home with a gardening tool
if it showed interest.

700
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:33,687
Use the frosted glasses.

701
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:35,689
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

702
00:56:35,880 --> 00:56:39,885
- I warmed up some chicken.
- That's the girl I love!

703
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:44,688
I'll only say this: You've always
been responsible with Ray.

704
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:48,607
He shouldn't hear
a strange man's voice here.

705
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:52,811
- Some drunken stranger.
- As opposed to 10 angry women?

706
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:57,404
Lean forward. Okay, I've got it.

707
00:56:57,680 --> 00:57:00,524
It's still edible. Change your shirt.

708
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:09,044
Hi, Jerry.

709
00:57:10,800 --> 00:57:15,761
Hi, Ray. Aren't you
supposed to be in bed?

710
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:17,240
Yeah.

711
00:57:18,320 --> 00:57:22,370
Don't worry, I won't tell.

712
00:57:23,280 --> 00:57:26,762
The human head weighs eight pounds.

713
00:57:37,800 --> 00:57:40,690
- Jerry Maguire.
- I think it's this one.

714
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:48,041
<i>You should dream about me.
I should be on your mind constantly.</i>

715
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:52,404
<i>That's when the dollars will flow.
The kwan will appear.</i>

716
00:57:52,600 --> 00:57:56,650
- Who is this?
- Who is this? This is the Rod Tidwell.

717
00:57:56,880 --> 00:57:59,167
I need to speak with my agent.

718
00:57:59,360 --> 00:58:02,443
- We should be one.
- You a football player?

719
00:58:02,920 --> 00:58:07,244
<i>A football player? I'm a teacher
about to whomp your ass!</i>

720
00:58:07,440 --> 00:58:09,169
Put Jerry on the phone!

721
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:12,921
You just can't fall
for some drowning man.

722
00:58:13,160 --> 00:58:14,969
- Be practical.
- Practical?

723
00:58:15,160 --> 00:58:18,767
Turtleneck, sensible.
V-neck, sexy. Turtleneck.

724
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:23,807
Don't say that. What are other women
my age doing right now?

725
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:27,368
They're out partying,
trying to get a man.

726
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:31,650
Trying to keep a man.
Not me, I'm trying to raise a man.

727
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:37,450
This one. I've got a 24-hour-a-day
reminder of Roger for my whole life.

728
00:58:37,640 --> 00:58:42,123
- I've had three lovers in four years.
- That's not bad.

729
00:58:42,360 --> 00:58:47,048
All of them ran a distant second
to a good book and a warm bath.

730
00:58:47,240 --> 00:58:51,450
Look at me. I'm the oldest
26-year-old in the world.

731
00:58:51,680 --> 00:58:53,808
- Now, how do I look?
- Good.

732
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:55,851
Yeah? Thanks.

733
00:58:56,040 --> 00:59:00,489
<i>72% of new buyers are
African-American. That's what I am.</i>

734
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:05,044
- You talk too much.
- Talking is primitive communication.

735
00:59:05,240 --> 00:59:08,642
- It was fun talking to you. Bye.
- Jerry...!

736
00:59:09,560 --> 00:59:13,201
<i>- I'll</i> make a ham sandwich.
- I wanna say one thing.

737
00:59:13,440 --> 00:59:17,570
- You do listen to me.
- Well, I love you. Mayo?

738
00:59:17,800 --> 00:59:20,565
...Repression, as a religion.

739
00:59:20,760 --> 00:59:24,845
When my daddy retired from
the United Way after 38 years...

740
00:59:25,160 --> 00:59:30,087
...he said, "I wish they'd given me
a more comfortable chair."

741
00:59:30,320 --> 00:59:31,970
And then my dad died.

742
00:59:32,200 --> 00:59:36,569
My mom took me to the zoo,
and I loved the zoo. And...

743
00:59:36,800 --> 00:59:37,926
Wait.

744
00:59:38,200 --> 00:59:42,967
- I want to tell you more about my dad.
- No, let's go to the zoo.

745
00:59:46,320 --> 00:59:47,765
You're right.

746
00:59:48,040 --> 00:59:52,409
It's just my whole life,
I've been trying to talk.

747
00:59:52,680 --> 00:59:55,081
I mean, really talk.

748
00:59:55,360 --> 00:59:59,160
But no one wants to listen.
You know that feeling?

749
00:59:59,400 --> 01:00:03,450
- They just look at you...
- Let's go to the zoo, right now.

750
01:00:03,680 --> 01:00:08,402
The zoo, you know...
The fucking zoo's closed.

751
01:00:11,360 --> 01:00:13,408
You said "fuck."

752
01:00:14,520 --> 01:00:16,522
Yeah, I did.

753
01:00:17,040 --> 01:00:19,281
- Is that...?
- I won't tell.

754
01:00:22,240 --> 01:00:27,201
Well, then I'm gonna
have to take you to the zoo.

755
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:33,481
- I gotta go to bed, my mom's coming.
- Oh, wait...

756
01:00:34,720 --> 01:00:37,530
I hear my mom. I gotta go to bed.

757
01:00:38,040 --> 01:00:40,930
- Thanks for listening.
- Sure.

758
01:00:42,840 --> 01:00:47,402
Okay. Drinks, food,
and I called you a cab.

759
01:00:49,920 --> 01:00:53,766
- Good idea.
- Quiet, I have a little boy asleep.

760
01:00:56,040 --> 01:00:57,087
Right.

761
01:00:58,000 --> 01:00:59,047
Our company.

762
01:01:03,280 --> 01:01:08,241
Look. A little...
A little speech before I go.

763
01:01:13,560 --> 01:01:18,407
Do not worry about your future.

764
01:01:18,760 --> 01:01:23,687
You and your son,
we, are just fine.

765
01:01:23,920 --> 01:01:25,763
You still have a job.

766
01:01:26,360 --> 01:01:31,400
But let me tell you something
about Jerry Maguire, okay?

767
01:01:31,640 --> 01:01:35,804
You come after me, and you will lose.

768
01:01:36,560 --> 01:01:41,282
No, because I am a survivor.
I'm a survivor!

769
01:01:41,920 --> 01:01:47,324
Dorothy Boyd, you are
with the Lord of the Living Room.

770
01:01:47,680 --> 01:01:50,650
The King of the Kingdom!

771
01:01:50,880 --> 01:01:53,087
And I am...

772
01:01:57,120 --> 01:01:58,201
...drunk.

773
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:09,564
We meet again.

774
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:25,087
Here.

775
01:02:35,160 --> 01:02:36,685
Truth?

776
01:02:38,440 --> 01:02:43,128
- Sure.
- I care about the job, of course.

777
01:02:43,360 --> 01:02:46,762
But mostly,
I just want to be inspired.

778
01:02:48,840 --> 01:02:52,367
- Me too.
- What you wrote inspired me.

779
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:59,047
I'm working with you
because of that memo.

780
01:03:00,880 --> 01:03:02,689
I loved that memo.

781
01:03:06,560 --> 01:03:08,608
It's a mission statement.

782
01:03:22,120 --> 01:03:23,610
Well...

783
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:26,931
Sorry about the hand.

784
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:33,611
You know that feeling?

785
01:03:33,880 --> 01:03:37,566
You're not completely
embarrassed yet...

786
01:03:37,800 --> 01:03:41,009
...but you glimpse
tomorrow's embarrassment?

787
01:03:41,200 --> 01:03:44,249
Don't worry about it, boss.

788
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:47,127
Oh, shit. You said "boss."

789
01:03:47,320 --> 01:03:50,767
- Yeah, I did.
- Now I feel like Clarence Thomas.

790
01:03:50,960 --> 01:03:55,443
- No, don't feel like Clarence Thomas.
- I do. I feel like him.

791
01:03:55,680 --> 01:04:00,447
- I'm, like, harassing you right now.
- Well, I may not sue.

792
01:04:13,280 --> 01:04:15,647
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

793
01:04:18,680 --> 01:04:21,684
Look, don't worry, okay?
I mean, don't...

794
01:04:23,960 --> 01:04:27,681
We'll be okay because
I am gonna take my one client...

795
01:04:29,240 --> 01:04:32,005
...and we are gonna go all the way.

796
01:04:33,680 --> 01:04:37,287
Because, hey...
I'm back.

797
01:04:39,680 --> 01:04:42,001
Don't worry.

798
01:04:57,320 --> 01:05:01,609
- Way to go, Rod. Good catch.
- You can't...

799
01:05:02,880 --> 01:05:05,008
All right, good job.

800
01:05:07,920 --> 01:05:13,006
- Gotta talk about his contract, Dennis.
- Meet me at The Crocodile, 8:00.

801
01:05:14,000 --> 01:05:15,365
You bet.

802
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:36,686
Thank you.

803
01:05:36,880 --> 01:05:40,646
<i>Tell me you got lost.
I thought I was your friend.</i>

804
01:05:40,840 --> 01:05:45,209
- Something came up.
- Okay. $10 <i>million</i> for four years.

805
01:05:45,400 --> 01:05:48,529
- You're dreaming.
- Ten for four. It's a deal.

806
01:05:50,200 --> 01:05:54,888
- He's got an attitude problem.
- He listens to me. I can help you.

807
01:05:55,080 --> 01:05:59,529
- He's a shrimp.
- He broke all the records last year.

808
01:05:59,760 --> 01:06:03,810
I want a prototypical
wide receiver who's 6'3", 220.

809
01:06:04,040 --> 01:06:07,249
<i>Not some guy who's 5'10" and bitches.</i>

810
01:06:07,480 --> 01:06:10,848
Dennis, I'm asking you...

811
01:06:12,560 --> 01:06:13,607
...for a favor.

812
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:19,446
<i>I introduced you to your wife.
We've spent Christmases together.</i>

813
01:06:19,640 --> 01:06:23,770
- Holiday cheer.
- Jerry, you're reaching.

814
01:06:24,000 --> 01:06:28,608
I'm asking for a favor.
Don't do this to me. We have history.

815
01:06:28,800 --> 01:06:33,647
We got history, all right.
You drove the prices up for years.

816
01:06:33,880 --> 01:06:39,284
- It's your turn at the end of the line.
- Dennis, don't...

817
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:48,363
I talked with Dennis Wilburn
about your renegotiation.

818
01:06:52,720 --> 01:06:54,006
Talking?

819
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:59,884
Jerry Rice, Andre Reed, Chris Carter.
I smoked all these fools!

820
01:07:00,960 --> 01:07:03,691
Yet they're making the big dollars.

821
01:07:03,920 --> 01:07:08,608
They are making the kwan.
And you're talking.

822
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:15,800
- Kwan? That's your word?
- Hell yeah, that's my word.

823
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:19,971
Some dudes might have coin,
but they'll never have kwan.

824
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:21,286
What is...?

825
01:07:21,480 --> 01:07:26,930
It means love, respect, community
and dollars. The entire package.

826
01:07:29,120 --> 01:07:30,121
The kwan.

827
01:07:31,200 --> 01:07:32,406
Great word.

828
01:07:34,480 --> 01:07:37,404
- Towel?
- No, I air-dry.

829
01:07:38,920 --> 01:07:44,370
Listen, Rod. I say this
with great respect for you.

830
01:07:45,640 --> 01:07:49,406
But those players you mentioned
are marquee players.

831
01:07:51,080 --> 01:07:55,005
- And this deal where, you know, we...
- Marquee?

832
01:07:55,200 --> 01:07:58,886
This is a renegotiation.
We want more from them.

833
01:07:59,080 --> 01:08:02,527
Show them your pure joy of the game.

834
01:08:02,760 --> 01:08:05,604
Bury the attitude a bit,
and show them...

835
01:08:05,840 --> 01:08:07,205
Wait.

836
01:08:07,680 --> 01:08:11,366
- You're telling me to dance.
- No. I'm saying...

837
01:08:12,080 --> 01:08:16,051
...to get back to the guy
who first started playing.

838
01:08:16,240 --> 01:08:21,201
Way back when you were a kid, it
wasn't just about the money, was it?

839
01:08:22,040 --> 01:08:23,485
Was it?

840
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:25,726
Was it?

841
01:08:27,880 --> 01:08:31,441
Do your job.
Don't you tell me to dance!

842
01:08:31,680 --> 01:08:33,489
- Fine.
- Hey. Hey!

843
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:35,409
I am an athlete.

844
01:08:35,680 --> 01:08:38,081
- I am not an entertainer!
- Fine!

845
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:43,730
I do not dance, and I do not start
pre-season without a contract!

846
01:08:44,240 --> 01:08:47,926
- Fine, fine, fine!
- Jerry, talk to me.

847
01:08:49,080 --> 01:08:51,845
Breathe! Breathe, Jerry.

848
01:08:54,320 --> 01:08:56,766
I am out here for you.

849
01:08:57,560 --> 01:09:00,643
You don't know
what it's like to be me.

850
01:09:00,840 --> 01:09:04,970
It is an up-at-dawn,
pride-swallowing siege...

851
01:09:05,240 --> 01:09:08,926
...that I will never fully
tell you about, okay?!

852
01:09:12,280 --> 01:09:13,725
God. Help me!

853
01:09:14,840 --> 01:09:17,923
Help me, Rod. Help me help you.

854
01:09:19,240 --> 01:09:22,881
Help me help you.

855
01:09:23,520 --> 01:09:26,444
Help me help you.

856
01:09:33,360 --> 01:09:35,010
I'm sorry.

857
01:09:36,120 --> 01:09:40,250
You are hanging on
by a very thin thread.

858
01:09:41,280 --> 01:09:43,362
And I dig that about you!

859
01:09:45,280 --> 01:09:49,444
No contract? I'll help me,
I'll help you, help everybody!

860
01:09:49,840 --> 01:09:54,368
- That's my man.
- Hey, I'm happy to entertain you.

861
01:09:54,560 --> 01:09:56,847
Help me! Help me!

862
01:09:58,520 --> 01:10:02,809
- See you in Los Angeles.
- Jerry. Come on, man.

863
01:10:03,200 --> 01:10:06,010
See, that's the difference between us.

864
01:10:06,200 --> 01:10:10,000
You think we're fighting.
I think we're talking.

865
01:10:14,720 --> 01:10:18,850
Unless you love everybody,
you can't sell anybody.

866
01:10:28,800 --> 01:10:33,681
Dennis Wilburn is faxing his offer
for Tidwell on Thursday morning.

867
01:10:33,880 --> 01:10:37,726
- He said you'd be happy... Glad.
- He say happy or glad?

868
01:10:39,320 --> 01:10:42,130
Glad. He said glad. Glad.

869
01:10:43,320 --> 01:10:47,962
- Glad is good.
- We could sure use that commission.

870
01:10:48,160 --> 01:10:52,165
Here. I did a rundown
on where you stand financially.

871
01:10:55,480 --> 01:11:00,327
- My condo was devalued.
- You don't have to explain.

872
01:11:01,000 --> 01:11:04,607
The other night, I wanna apologize.

873
01:11:04,840 --> 01:11:06,763
What happened there?

874
01:11:06,960 --> 01:11:10,248
We're coworkers.
We can't have atmosphere.

875
01:11:10,440 --> 01:11:12,841
I'm very relieved you said that.

876
01:11:13,080 --> 01:11:16,402
You know, the other night,
I was lonely.

877
01:11:16,600 --> 01:11:18,967
I felt you understood something.

878
01:11:19,960 --> 01:11:22,770
We've got a company to think about.

879
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:26,049
I'll never take advantage
of you again.

880
01:11:26,440 --> 01:11:29,603
- Good.
- You walked out on a job for me.

881
01:11:29,880 --> 01:11:31,882
Can this be right?

882
01:11:32,880 --> 01:11:34,041
Exactly.

883
01:11:35,400 --> 01:11:39,371
I know you need to be alone
with your thoughts.

884
01:11:39,560 --> 01:11:42,689
Think about what's wrong
and how to fix it.

885
01:11:42,920 --> 01:11:45,571
And, you know, just be alone.

886
01:11:46,120 --> 01:11:47,884
Alone.

887
01:11:53,880 --> 01:11:57,521
- You wanna go out to dinner?
- I know a great place.

888
01:11:57,720 --> 01:12:02,248
I broke up with that loser,
and then he started stalking me.

889
01:12:02,440 --> 01:12:06,843
- What do you mean by stalking?
- Coming over uninvited.

890
01:12:07,320 --> 01:12:12,042
"Coming over uninvited"? So Romeo
on your balcony is a stalker?

891
01:12:22,920 --> 01:12:25,161
Excuse me. Ladies?

892
01:12:26,560 --> 01:12:31,248
Good evening,
I'm looking for Dorothy Boyd.

893
01:12:31,720 --> 01:12:36,442
- She's in the kitchen.
- Laurel. Hello.

894
01:12:37,760 --> 01:12:42,243
- Where are you taking her tonight?
- You're the nanny?

895
01:12:43,200 --> 01:12:45,601
- Au pair.
- Au pair? I see.

896
01:12:51,240 --> 01:12:52,446
He likes you.

897
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:57,163
My goodness.
I've got some gifts for you.

898
01:12:58,200 --> 01:13:01,682
Do you like presents?
Good, all right.

899
01:13:02,360 --> 01:13:06,365
Arizona Cardinals.
It's the team Rod plays for.

900
01:13:06,560 --> 01:13:10,042
- Dropping your laundry off?
- Want a Steelers hat?

901
01:13:10,280 --> 01:13:12,806
- For me?
- I got some things.

902
01:13:13,000 --> 01:13:15,571
- I've got it in gray too.
- Thanks.

903
01:13:15,800 --> 01:13:19,486
You're very welcome.
Look what I've got here.

904
01:13:19,680 --> 01:13:23,002
An energy bar.
It'll keep you up all night.

905
01:13:23,160 --> 01:13:27,484
That's not a good idea.
Aunt Laurel will eat that.

906
01:13:30,480 --> 01:13:33,165
It looks like you've got a fan.

907
01:13:35,280 --> 01:13:39,365
That's more than a dress,
that's an Audrey Hepburn movie.

908
01:13:39,600 --> 01:13:43,810
I got revved up at the thought
of an evening among adults.

909
01:13:44,000 --> 01:13:47,004
- No offense, buddy.
- Jerry, you meet Chad?

910
01:13:47,200 --> 01:13:50,522
Am I dressed okay? I didn't realize...

911
01:13:54,840 --> 01:13:57,207
Don't let him stay up too late.

912
01:13:57,400 --> 01:14:01,849
Tonight, I'm gonna teach
Ray about jazz.

913
01:14:02,080 --> 01:14:04,321
That'll put him to sleep early.

914
01:14:06,040 --> 01:14:07,883
I want to go too.

915
01:14:08,080 --> 01:14:13,405
No, sweetheart, you stay here
with Chad and be good. Kiss me.

916
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:15,925
Let's go.

917
01:14:18,320 --> 01:14:19,970
- Good night.
- Good night.

918
01:14:20,160 --> 01:14:22,162
Give me a hug.

919
01:15:04,240 --> 01:15:07,449
<i>- I'll</i> meet you at the car.
- Okay.

920
01:15:07,680 --> 01:15:09,682
You forgot your keys.

921
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:14,124
I've never seen him kiss a man
just like a dad!

922
01:15:14,600 --> 01:15:18,969
Wasn't that thrilling?
He must have been needing that.

923
01:15:19,200 --> 01:15:23,683
Don't cry at the start of a date.
Cry at the end, like I do.

924
01:15:24,840 --> 01:15:28,128
Don't be a shoulder
for him to cry on either.

925
01:15:28,360 --> 01:15:31,011
- Keys.
- Oh, keys.

926
01:15:32,440 --> 01:15:34,124
Oh, dear.

927
01:15:59,720 --> 01:16:03,520
Ever since you've met me, I've been...

928
01:16:08,440 --> 01:16:12,889
It was laziness, my breakup
with Avery. You know that saying?

929
01:16:13,080 --> 01:16:17,768
"It's nobody's fault." It's a lie.
Somebody is always to blame.

930
01:16:17,960 --> 01:16:21,965
You go for it like you do a job.
You work at it.

931
01:16:22,160 --> 01:16:26,370
But maybe love shouldn't be
such hard work.

932
01:16:27,600 --> 01:16:29,807
Yeah, maybe so.

933
01:16:30,920 --> 01:16:35,847
But it's not every day
you say goodbye to a woman like that.

934
01:16:38,080 --> 01:16:41,368
- A song for the lovers?
- No, thank you.

935
01:16:41,560 --> 01:16:46,964
- No, no, we work together.
- This is like an office meeting.

936
01:16:47,760 --> 01:16:49,808
But I know what you mean.

937
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:55,850
It wasn't like my marriage to Roger
was any good, even before...

938
01:16:58,320 --> 01:17:00,049
Before...?

939
01:17:02,000 --> 01:17:04,321
- Jerry?
- What?

940
01:17:05,240 --> 01:17:08,369
Let's not tell our sad stories.

941
01:17:13,040 --> 01:17:16,567
I'll be back in just a second, okay?

942
01:17:45,960 --> 01:17:49,646
They sting. Let Chad
catch the bee in the glass.

943
01:17:49,840 --> 01:17:54,880
He won't hurt him. You've got such
a good heart, buddy. I love you.

944
01:18:23,200 --> 01:18:26,568
Well, this would be good night.

945
01:18:27,280 --> 01:18:28,691
