02:05:21,280 --> 02:05:23,282
I love you!

1408
02:05:28,320 --> 02:05:31,688
I love you, Tyson.
I love you, baby.

1409
02:05:31,880 --> 02:05:34,531
How's the baby? How's Katie?

1410
02:05:35,240 --> 02:05:38,130
Oh, I love you so much.

1411
02:05:39,640 --> 02:05:42,883
You know ain't nothing
gonna happen to me.

1412
02:05:51,240 --> 02:05:56,246
The problem is, like you were
saying earlier, the biorhythms.

1413
02:05:57,680 --> 02:06:00,809
I was saying
the neural pathways are set.

1414
02:06:01,000 --> 02:06:05,847
That's why it's hard
for people to change.

1415
02:06:09,520 --> 02:06:14,208
I'm sorry, these stupid holidays
make me feel more divorced.

1416
02:06:14,640 --> 02:06:19,362
You know? With the songs,
the constant chocolate-eating...

1417
02:06:35,360 --> 02:06:38,364
I have a confession to make.

1418
02:06:38,840 --> 02:06:43,721
I've listened to you all
tell a thousand sob stories.

1419
02:06:43,920 --> 02:06:46,321
I've been very judgmental.

1420
02:06:46,520 --> 02:06:50,809
Maybe you're all correct.
Men are the enemy.

1421
02:06:51,040 --> 02:06:54,601
No, they're not the enemy.

1422
02:06:54,840 --> 02:06:58,208
But I still love the enemy.

1423
02:07:12,080 --> 02:07:13,366
Hello.

1424
02:07:15,840 --> 02:07:18,207
I'm looking for my wife.

1425
02:07:30,720 --> 02:07:31,881
Wait.

1426
02:07:42,240 --> 02:07:46,768
If this is where it has to happen,
then it's where it happens.

1427
02:07:47,880 --> 02:07:52,807
I'm not letting you get rid of me.
How about that?

1428
02:07:58,360 --> 02:08:02,570
This used to be my specialty.
I was good in a living room.

1429
02:08:02,760 --> 02:08:04,410
I'd do it alone.

1430
02:08:05,160 --> 02:08:07,208
And now, I just...

1431
02:08:13,280 --> 02:08:14,691
I don't know.

1432
02:08:20,200 --> 02:08:22,009
But tonight...

1433
02:08:22,920 --> 02:08:28,290
...our little project, our company
had a very big night.

1434
02:08:28,800 --> 02:08:33,044
A very, very big night.

1435
02:08:36,000 --> 02:08:38,048
But it wasn't complete.

1436
02:08:40,560 --> 02:08:46,169
It wasn't nearly close to being
in the same vicinity as complete...

1437
02:08:46,640 --> 02:08:49,325
...because I couldn't
share it with you.

1438
02:08:50,640 --> 02:08:52,688
I couldn't hear your voice...

1439
02:08:55,000 --> 02:08:57,651
...or laugh about it with you.

1440
02:09:00,040 --> 02:09:03,203
I missed my... I missed my wife.

1441
02:09:19,560 --> 02:09:24,771
We live in a cynical world.
A cynical world.

1442
02:09:25,240 --> 02:09:29,962
And we work in a business
of tough competitors.

1443
02:09:39,640 --> 02:09:41,449
I love you.

1444
02:09:41,680 --> 02:09:43,125
You...

1445
02:09:44,880 --> 02:09:46,644
...complete me.

1446
02:09:48,080 --> 02:09:50,162
- And I just...
- Shut up.

1447
02:09:51,520 --> 02:09:53,124
Just shut up.

1448
02:09:53,880 --> 02:09:56,042
You had me at "hello."

1449
02:09:57,240 --> 02:09:59,607
You had me at "hello."

1450
02:10:12,160 --> 02:10:14,891
This is my best discussion group.

1451
02:10:15,080 --> 02:10:19,802
Your father leaves home on Christmas
Eve, abandoning your family.

1452
02:10:20,040 --> 02:10:24,489
Your mother had to sweep up
at the prison to pay your tuition.

1453
02:10:24,920 --> 02:10:28,288
Your brother lost a leg
in a fishing accident.

1454
02:10:28,480 --> 02:10:32,565
You've had a list of horrific
things happen in your life.

1455
02:10:32,800 --> 02:10:36,441
- I'm not gonna cry, Roy.
- I've got some good news.

1456
02:10:36,680 --> 02:10:39,570
I've just been handed a signed memo.

1457
02:10:39,760 --> 02:10:43,970
It's a contract.
Arizona Cardinals. Four years.

1458
02:10:44,160 --> 02:10:49,326
$11.2 million and you'll play
in your home state, where it started.

1459
02:10:49,520 --> 02:10:51,488
What do you think of that?

1460
02:11:11,560 --> 02:11:16,202
I love everybody.
I love my wife! Marcee!

1461
02:11:17,440 --> 02:11:21,570
I love my kids!
Tyson and my new baby, Katie.

1462
02:11:21,760 --> 02:11:26,891
My older brother, who got one leg,
and my younger brother, Tee Pee.

1463
02:11:27,080 --> 02:11:30,846
You're militant, but I ain't
mad at you. I love you.

1464
02:11:31,040 --> 02:11:34,169
I love my teammates.
I'm omitting someone.

1465
02:11:34,480 --> 02:11:39,691
- We only have a half-hour show.
- I send love to my offensive line.

1466
02:11:40,680 --> 02:11:44,890
Nice to see you. Congratulations.
Good for you.

1467
02:11:45,560 --> 02:11:48,769
You remember Troy
from the Super Bowl?

1468
02:11:48,960 --> 02:11:50,007
We met in '93.

1469
02:11:50,160 --> 02:11:53,482
- That's right. I enjoyed your memo.
- Thank you.

1470
02:11:53,840 --> 02:11:58,846
- A little slow but you come around.
- We're out of time.

1471
02:11:59,040 --> 02:12:01,008
I'm forgetting somebody.

1472
02:12:02,680 --> 02:12:04,728
Jerry Maguire...

1473
02:12:05,400 --> 02:12:07,209
...my agent.

1474
02:12:10,400 --> 02:12:13,529
You are my ambassador of kwan, man.

1475
02:12:15,000 --> 02:12:19,085
Thank you. Congratulations.
We'll be right back.

1476
02:12:22,920 --> 02:12:27,448
- How did you like the zoo, buddy?
- It was great!

1477
02:12:27,640 --> 02:12:29,722
One, two, three.

1478
02:12:33,240 --> 02:12:35,447
Hey, kid, throw the ball.

1479
02:12:45,600 --> 02:12:46,931
Good throw, man.

1480
02:12:49,960 --> 02:12:51,644
Did you see?

1481
02:12:52,280 --> 02:12:54,965
Oh, no. Let's go.

1482
02:12:55,400 --> 02:13:00,406
What? I'm not saying we'll throw him
into the major leagues tomorrow...

1483
02:13:00,600 --> 02:13:03,410
...but he's got natural talent.

1484
02:13:03,600 --> 02:13:08,128
I know the right people
that'll help develop his talent.

1485
02:13:21,120 --> 02:13:24,169
Hey, I don't have all the answers.

1486
02:13:24,400 --> 02:13:29,850
In life, to be honest, I've failed
as much as I've succeeded.

1487
02:13:30,160 --> 02:13:33,721
But I love my wife,
I love my life...

1488
02:13:33,920 --> 02:13:36,764
...and I wish you my kind of success.

